snippet: Temple had not beaten Penn State since 1941, but P. J. Walker’s go-ahead touchdown in the third quarter propelled the Owls to a 27-10 victory.
abstract: College Football East Roundup; Temple University defeats Penn State, 27-10, winning matchup for first time since 1941; other football news noted.
lead_paragraph: Temple had not beaten Penn State since 1941, but P. J. Walker’s go-ahead touchdown in the third quarter propelled the Owls to a 27-10 victory.

headline.print_headline: Temple Ends Long Drought by Defeating Penn State
headline.main: Temple Ends Long Drought by Defeating Penn State
